rank of a matrix 10K – 100K Low
The dimension of the column space of a matrix is called its rank. - rank of 1 - when the output of the matrix multiplication is a line (for next article) - rank of 2 - when all the outputs of the matrix mult land in 2-D, then matrix has a rank of 2. - etc&hellip;
It is the number of linearly independent columns
